  "name": "Morrison COU1 \u2014 CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (expanded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: Since original validation campaign completion (2023-Q2), the approved operating envelope has been extended to include paediatric patients (cardiac index 1.8\u20132.4 L/min/m\u00b2) and high-viscosity perfusate conditions (haematocrit 36\u201342%). Re-validation covering these expanded conditions is planned but has not yet been completed; no new ValidationResult is linked for the expanded range.",
