    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must span operating conditions representative of the COU; Gradation 2 requires coverage of primary intended use regime.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities (morrison-vr-001, morrison-vr-002) cover the original adult CPB operating envelope (5 flow-speed points, haematocrit 33%). These activities were representative of the COU at the time of validation completion (2023-Q2). The COU has since been expanded to include paediatric patients and high-viscosity perfusate; the existing validation activities do not cover this expanded regime. Re-validation is planned for 2025-Q3. Current credibility evidence is assessed as meeting Gradation 2 for the originally validated envelope only; interim acceptance is documented in the decision record."
